{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"72433525-968d-4ac3-82fb-84b404fcc9f9","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**1. In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n- **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n- **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces both the framework and adapter)\n- **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.2\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**2. In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:**\n\nNo changes needed — `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, and `Assert.*` all work the same under the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace in MSTest v3.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| Assembly ref to `QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` | `MSTest` 3.8.2 NuGet package |\n| `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0 | `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.12.0 |\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e3dbf202-0ef0-4c6f-a9a4-9a24c1eaf7e2","outputTokens":338,"requestId":"BC25:35F104:216025E:2528374:69FAA635"},"id":"4390d69c-d005-44da-8756-8087851afb89","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:23:57.052Z","parentId":"d258dbc9-328e-41a9-8630-f221454171d0"}
